data.title: Corbera, Valencia, Spain
data.text:
Corbera, Valencia, Spain, also known as Corbera de Alcira, is a municipality located in the Ribera Alta comarca, with a latitude of 39.1500000 and longitude of -0.3500000 in the time zone of Europe/Madrid. The town has a rich history and heritage, with notable landmarks including the Church of San Jaime and the Palace of the Counts of Corbera. The climate is typically Mediterranean, with hot summers and mild winters.
